I say dumb things, you say dumb things.
But Kohn went with “business owners.” It almost seems too absurd to not be a parody account.
When the business can’t make payroll, what other option do the business owners have?
What’s particularly gross about this is that it cheapens the real pain being felt by many of these business owners whose employees are like family to them.
Thankfully, judging by the ungodly ratio her intellectually offensive post accrued, it’s safe to say I’m not alone in my indignation.